    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There is also an issue with the `merge` function that has a `copy` parameter, but it doesn't do anything.\n\n```\ncopy : boolean, default True\n    If False, do not copy data unnecessarily\n```\n\nBut it does, even if the index is the same object.\n\n``` python\n>>> index = pd.Int64Index([1,2])\n>>> df1 = pd.DataFrame([[1,2],[3,4]], index=index, columns=['a', 'b'])\n>>> df2 = pd.DataFrame([[5,6],[7,8]], index=index, columns=['c', 'd'])\n>>> df = df1.merge(df2, left_index=True, right_index=True, copy=False)\n>>> df.iloc[0, 0] = 42\n>>> df\n    a  b  c  d\n1  42  2  5  6\n2   3  4  7  8\n>>> df1\n   a  b\n1  1  2\n2  3  4\n```\n"
  },
